  v1 REJECT: REJECT: Scenario 2 (JSON mode, no changes) does NOT match spec. Spec requires EXACTLY compact {"changes":[],"message":"No active changes."} (2 fields, single line). Impl at src/commands/workflow/status.ts:70-72 does JSON.stringify({changes:[],message:'No active changes.',root:rootOutput}, null, 2) — TWO violations:

D1 (BLOCKER) Extra field: impl emits a third 'root' field ({path,source}) absent from spec. Actual stdout hexdump confirms "root":{"path":"/tmp/v1-empty","source":"nearest"}. Spec field set is exactly {changes,message}.

D2 (BLOCKER) Serialization form: impl pretty-prints with 2-space indent (null,2); spec requires compact single-line JSON. Actual output is multi-line indented, not {"changes":[],"message":"No active changes."}.

D3 (MAJOR) Weakened test: test/commands/artifact-workflow.test.ts:145-151 ('exits gracefully with JSON when no changes exist') only asserts json.changes==[] and json.message=='No active changes.' — it never checks the field set (no extra 'root') nor compact serialization, so D1/D2 pass CI undetected. This is precisely how the defect shipped.

Verified PASSING scenarios (so the defect is isolated):
- Scenario 1 (text, empty): stdout exactly 'No active changes. Create one with: openspec new change <name>', exit 0. (spinner '- Loading change status...' is ora on stderr, not stdout — OK.) status.ts:78.
- Scenario 3 (changes exist, no --change): throws 'Missing required option --change. Available changes:\n  feat-x', exit 1. status.ts:82-85. Matches spec '...Available changes: ...'.
- Scenario 4 (--change non-existent, others exist): throws "Change 'non-existent' not found. Available changes:\n  feat-x", exit 1. Contains required substring; consistent with requirement 'continue to throw errors as before' (validateChangeExists unchanged). status.ts via shared.ts:124-127.
- Scenario 5: 'instructions' still throws original 'No changes found. Create one with: openspec new change <name>' (shared.ts:104) — unaffected. 'show' emits pre-existing 'Nothing to show...' (its own no-arg path, never reaches validateChangeExists) — also unaffected by this change.

Conclusion: Scenario 2 fails byte-for-byte on BOTH field set (D1) and serialization form (D2); the test was weakened to not catch it (D3). Verdict rules require EVERY scenario to match byte-for-byte → REJECT.
